    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-07-18T17:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-07-18T17:25:00-05:00" n="118"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                <head>118. Circular Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    to <gloss type="to">All Diplomatic Missions in the American Republics</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d118fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 361/7–1856. Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MRB1"
                            >Memminger</persName> and approved by <persName corresp="#p_HHF1"
                            >Holland</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-07-18T18:25:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1956—6:25 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>37. President <persName>Eisenhower</persName> considering proposing in speech at
                    Panama each American President name personal and trusted representative to join
                    in preparing concrete recommendations for making <gloss target="#t_OAS1"
                        >OAS</gloss> more effective instrument in those fields of cooperative effort
                    that affect the welfare of our peoples. Presidents could look to these
                    representatives for practical suggestions in economic, financial, social and
                    technical fields which <gloss target="#t_OAS1">OAS</gloss> might usefully
                    adopt.</p>
                <p>You may discuss this proposal in strict confidence with President your country to
                    ascertain whether he has any objection since President
                        <persName>Eisenhower</persName> would like to put proposal forward as idea
                    viewed favorably by Presidents meeting Panama.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
